mention.text: `` Dreamer , '' an imagined account of the last days of the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.
a minister as well as a leader of the struggle for black rights
a shy , self-conscious 24-year - old acolyte of King
Matthew Bishop who , in the words of the woman he loves , talks like a thesaurus
his , which is so much clearer and bigger and cleaner
Matthew 's growth from a kind of intellectually precocious late adolescence to full manhood
the appearance of an entirely fictional character , Chaym Smith , a global wanderer and striver
a powerful character , eloquently irascible , morally deep
Chaym , whose homophonic resemblance to Cain is made explicit as Johnson returns again and again to his biblical theme
everyman as well , within and without
Chaym , asked by a pair of rather woodenly constructed FBI men to turn from double to double agent
the doppelganger , the double , the mirror image and the opposite
Cain , cursed with the burden of restlessness and the endless quest for selfhood
The biblical story of Cain , whose sacrifice was rather inexplicably rejected by God
betrayal involving an unlikely pair of federal agents and Chaym
an intentional reflection of the deeper incompleteness of real life
His recourse to a kind of unresolved and implausible mystery
the very embodiment of the blues
if a veil had lifted _ the tortured shadow of Cain everywhere , within me and without , his many cultural reincarnations parading through my mind like frames projected on a cyclorama
a nostrum , a commonplace sort of wisdom
